$interpreted: Law: This odor is spread throughout all of Maple Lake; yet they conceal themselves with great efficacy. Why on earth have they come?
Law: What a marvelous voice, and this song...
Hestia: You must be Yan-Bo's old friend, Law! My name's Hestia, welcome to Maple Lake!
Law: How does everyone know who I am?
Hestia: Everyone here is pretty close, so stuff gets around.
Hestia: With that huge lump on the left side of Pang's face, coupled with his enormous smile, I even didn't need a guess and knew what was going on~
Law: Hehe, quite an interesting damsel you are.
Law: Ah, yes. Was that ye splendid voice I just heard? Quite impressive.
Hestia: Uh-huh. You wanna hear some more?
Law: That would be splendid, please.
Law: Ah, yes, this tune...it comes from my homeland.
Hestia: Yan-Bo taught me that. He used to hum it many years ago, but I never could hear what he was singing about...took me forever to learn it.
Law: Ha...he practiced for a full three months. Maeok always said he was rotten wood that could not be sculpted.
Hestia: Who's...Maeok?
Law: Nothing. Hestia, I would like to ask something of ye.
Hestia: You talk funny, just like Yan-Bo. Ask anything you'd like!
Law: Besides this song, hast Yan-Bo...spoken of other matters from the East Alliance?
Hestia: Yan-Bo seldom speaks of his homeland. However, sometimes when he's really drunk he talks a lot about it.
Law: ...Drunk?
Hestia: Yah. I remember one time he was pounding liquor and saying a whole bunch of stuff to the moon.
Law: And what didst he speak of?
Hestia: I didn't really understand...something of revenge, imposter, stuff like that.
Hestia: Ah, he kept saying a name. Kept apologizing to whoever that was.
Hestia: Uh...I can't remember. Kuei, or something like that.
Law: All these years...yet he still hides away, conceals himself, unwilling to share his burdens with another...I suppose I can understand.
Law: That is...pent up frustration must be released, lest it be too hard to bear.
Hestia: Understand whâ€”
Hestia: That's the platypuses...
Hestia: Frogodilly, must be Karnulla causing trouble again. I'm gonna drown him in the darn pits of Maple Lake!
Law: Involving oneself in thine affairs is not the way of the warrior. But I must repay you for your gracious melody.
Law: As for this...I shall put it down for the moment be.
